value.value: Is a hyoid muscle that inserts at the most anterior basibranchial and also at the posterior ends of the ceratohyals and functions in jaw closure.
Is a hyoid muscle that attaches to the dorsomedial faces of the hyosymplectics.

label.value: pillar of the anterior semicircular canal
pillar of the lateral semicircular canal

value.value: Rod-like internal median skeletal support elememts of the anal fin, which articulate with the distal radial elements.
Radial elements are the internal skeletal supports of the median and paired fins.

definition.value: Radial elements may be cartilaginous or bony; always present at the base of fins; typically support lepidotrichia.

value.value: Pelvic fin radial elements are internal skeletal supports of the pelvic fin.
Endochondral element that is paired and supports the pelvic fin. The basipterygium has a posteromedial process called the ischiac process (Wietzman 1962).
Rod-like internal median skeletal support elements of the anal fin, which articulate with the lepidotrichia distally.
Rod-like internal median skeletal support elements of the dorsal fin, which articulate with the lepidotrichia distally.
Rod-like internal median skeletal support elements of the dorsal fin, which articulate with the distal radial elements.

Pectoral fin radial elements are the internal skeletal supports of the pectoral fin which develop from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc, supports the pectoral lepidotrichia or fin rays and connects the lepidotrichia with the primary pectoral girdle.

definition.value: There are two paired series of pectoral radial elements, the proximal and the distal ones that may have variable shapes and sizes.

value.value: Pectoral fin radial element which develops from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc, supports a few pectoral lepidotrichia or fin rays and connects the lepidotrichia and distal radial elements with the primary pectoral girdle (scapula and coracoid).

definition.value: Two to four flat or slightly rod-like proximal pectoral radial elements, bilaterally, can be found in teleosts. Pectoral proximal radial elements are commonly hour-glass or rectangular shaped. The presence of four pectoral proximal radial elements is interpreted as a synapomorphy of teleosts (Patterson 1977, Arratia 1999).

value.value: Pectoral fin radial element that sometimes ossifies, develops from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc, and is located at the proximal region of a lepidotrichium, between its hemitrichia. Pectoral fin distal radial element is paired.

definition.value: A variable number of pectoral distal radial elements may be present in each pectoral fin. They are commonly small elements, rod-like, round or square shaped.

value.value: Dorsal fin radial element that is the rod-like internal median skeletal support element of the dorsal fin located between the dorsal fin proximal radial element and dorsal fin distal radial element.

definition.value: Synonym dorsal fin medial radial from Weitzman, 1962.

value.value: Anal fin radial element that is the rod-like internal median skeletal support element of the anal fin located between the anal fin proximal radial element and anal fin distal radial element.

definition.value: Synonym anal fin medial radial from Weitzman, 1962.

value.value: Anal fin radial elements are internal skeletal supports of the anal fin.
Dorsal fin radial elements are internal skeletal supports of the dorsal fin.
